                "SILI",
                "SILI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Two Si(Li) detectors of 100 mumeters",
                "and 0.5 mm thicknesses were used as the telescope to",
                "detect charged particles at large angles (> 10",
                "degrees).  The energy resolution was about 600 keV."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The energy spectra for the angles (<10 degrees)",
                "were measured using a magnetic separator (MASE) which",
                "consisted of two dipole and five quadrupole magnets.",
                "A single 0.5 mm thick Si(Li) counter with the active",
                "area of about 20 mm in diameter was used to detect  the",
                "reaction  products.  The detector was placed at the end",
                "of the separator in the focal plane.  The  flight  path",
                "was 4 m."
              ]
            }
